			<div class="content" id="post-content-1933154">
									

<p>This guide has been rewritten as part of the 2014 background guide overhaul. The original version of this page can be found in archive form <a href="/security-clearance-levels-arc">here</a>.</p>
<h1><span>Changes From Original Version</span></h1>
<ul>
<li>Security Clearance Levels have been cleaned up and made more consistent with real-world security clearance systems, along with notes on &quot;need to know&quot; and how that works.</li>
<li>Class A-C have been defined, Class D has been cleaned up, and Class E has been reworked to maintain the original sentiment while making it more in line with A-D.</li>
<li>Class D personnel are no longer explicitly terminated at the end of the month; the new definition has more room for headcanon.</li>
<li>Class D personnel are no longer explicitly drawn from death row convict populations.</li>
<li>Added Employee Title short list to combat the perception that the Foundation is made up entirely of only &quot;Agents&quot;, &quot;Researchers&quot;, and &quot;O5s&quot;.</li>
</ul>
<h1><span>Credits</span></h1>
