														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1933201">
									

<p>A number of things I love about this revamp:</p>
<ul>
<li>It makes sense. It doesn't introduce a ton of logic holes, unlike the last system.</li>
<li>Level 0 through 5 now actually make <em>sense</em>. (As they should, given that Mann actually works with clearance levels, and Aelanna has done so as well!)</li>
<li>Level 5, &quot;Thaumiel&quot;, is a really fun addition to fluff. (I think that was Mann/Aelanna.)</li>
<li>Class A through C are fun, interesting additions, the kind of stuff that the last system was <em>trying</em> to use, except it merged them confusingly with clearance level and was too light on detail to actually be interesting.</li>
<li>Class D and Class E are excellent revamps of old concepts.</li>
<li>Class D (probably the most important part of the document) is completely compatible with current canon yet it no longer horribly breaks suspension of disbelief! This was a tough nut to crack, and I think what we came up with is excellent.</li>
<li>Staff Titles are now useful and make sense! Yay!</li>
<li>The Writing Guide is a really nice behind-the-curtain essay. I imagine it will be helpful to many.</li>
<li>Overall, this page is now actually extremely helpful to writers wanting to actually write shit about the Foundation!</li>
</ul>

							</div>

								
