				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/aelanna" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(334454); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=334454&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610202523" alt="Aelanna" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=334454)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/aelanna" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(334454); return false;" >Aelanna</a></span> <span class="odate time_1389459052 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">11 Jan 2014 16:50</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1933502">
									

<blockquote>
<p>Good and simple.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Good, simple, implausible, and incorrectly used. This overhaul came to be because common usage and staff interpretation disagreed with the actual words that were on it.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>I am saying this because many of the restrictions about A-C classes overlap or could be overlapped with the current clearances (O5s with As, Site directors with Bs) and so on with little effort.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>That's not the point. The point was to explain why we have a Class D when there's no A-C, something that actually comes up quite often when people ask you about Foundation backstory.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Also, I feel that D-classes somehow got the suspense and horror around them cut out with no real reason.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>The reason is because many people felt that this was implausibly and over-the-top ridiculous. It shattered peoples' suspension of disbelief because there simply aren't that many death row convicts around.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>A horrible thing that instills fear that the next civilian made into Ds can be literally <span style="text-decoration: underline;">YOU</span>.</p>
</blockquote>
<blockquote>
<p>Same with the monthly executions.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Many people would call this forced and contrived, rather than actual existential horror. Among those people also happen to be the majority of the administration.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>If this is a progress from the old &quot;scary and simple&quot; Foundation to the modern bureucratic Foundation [&#8230;] I don't think the steps mentioned above were good steps to take.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>As a reminder to everyone, these guides were overhauled with the direct input and blessing of most of the administration and staff. This represents what we have wanted the guides to be for a very long time &#8212; well over a year, in fact &#8212; and have been thoroughly edited over the course of literally months to address every minor detail.</p>

							</div>

								
					
