								<div class="title" id="post-title-1933505">
																		
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/aelanna" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(334454); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=334454&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610202523" alt="Aelanna" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=334454)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/aelanna" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(334454); return false;" >Aelanna</a></span> <span class="odate time_1389459422 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">11 Jan 2014 16:57</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1933505">
									

<blockquote>
<p>However, according to a lot of articles, it isn't <em>right</em>.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>If you have specific articles that contradict the new guide information, please bring them to my attention. This guide was created using a combination of old guide information, common site usage, and real-world security clearance procedure.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>[&#8230;] I can't think of any reason to have class A-C, unless it's being appended to the number clearance [&#8230;]</p>
</blockquote>
<p>A-C exist because newbies often ask what A-C are. This sliding scale also allowed us to fold E into the same scale, and thus streamline the entire concept of A-E. It also adds a further undertone of competence to the Foundation by implying that the Foundation has very sophisticated disaster response and recovery, something that is far more plausible than the royal clusterfuck that every containment breach seems to sound like. It's not intended to be appended to number clearances, nor does any of this require that articles be changed.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>There's no longer any room to breathe.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Of all the guides that were overhauled, this was the one with the least room for interpretation, the only major salient points being Class D personnel and titles. If there is any particular point that sticks out to you and makes you feel that it restricts your ability to write, then <em>by all means, please point them out</em>. The general intent of all of the guide overhauls was to create a medium that was more <em>inspiring</em> rather than <em>restrictive</em>; no one I have spoken to in the process of writing this felt that it unduly restricted anyone's ability to portray the Foundation within their personal headcanon.</p>

							</div>

								
					
